rtextualität des Rechts, historische und aktuelle (auf die europäische Einigung zurückzuführende) Wandlungen von Rechts- und Sprachsystemen, der Nutzen der Linguistik für die Kriminologie sowie Ursachen und Lösungen für die Schwerverständlichkeit von Gesetzen.  aThis volume presents a collection of contributions by linguists and lawyers on topical questions of the interconnections between language and law, and opens up a wide range of theoretical, methodological and practical approaches to aspects such as politics and the public domain, court proceedings, criminology, the editing of legislation, legal training, and the Europeanisation of law.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aLawxLanguage. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBaldauf, Christa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraselmann, Petra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusse, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristensen, Ralph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFalkson, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrießhaber, Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroot, Gerard-René de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHab-Zumkehr, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarras, 